subSubSection.paragraph:
Ventral surface
. Black, shiny; mesoventrum with white spot posterolaterally, metepiventrum with two small white spots, metepimeron with very small white longitudinal spot, joints of all legs with white spots (
Fig. 2
), each visible abdominal ventrite with small white strip laterally (
Fig. 2
).

Hypopharyngeal sclerome
(
Fig. 31
). Asymmetrical, truncate process strongly protruding, pointed. Tufts of tegumentary expansions (= phoba, sensu 
Böving 1936
) present on left lateral lobe, at base of truncate process, and proximal to right part of mesolateral margin of hypopharyngeal sclerome, the latter group may be absent in some individuals. Both lateral lobes only feebly sclerotized with approximately 15–20 setae.

Thorax
(
Fig. 24
). Prothorax with single dorsal lobe, meso- and metathorax with three well developed lobes. Dorsi of each thoracic sublobe with approximately 4–6 rows of setae, anterior rows with short setae, setae of posterior row(s) about 3– 
5x
as long as previous ones. Prothoracic sclerite well sclerotized, covering almost completely lateral portion of prothorax. Prothoracic spiracle (
Fig. 36
) with C-shaped respiratory plate; lobes of respiratory plate well separated with distance between lobes slightly shorter than the maximum diameter of respiratory plate. Respiratory plate with around 35 holes across diameter. All pairs of legs (
Figs. 37–39
) subequal in shape and size. Pretarsi cylindrical with 11–13 setae, claw absent.
